    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3ec8a9a2_07263a21",
        "filename": "snapshot/linux/exception_snapshot_linux_test.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 173,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-01T21:04:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The timer_t used by (g)libc (secretly a pointer to an internal timer struct) is not the same as the __kernel_timer_t we expect to get in Codes()[0].\n\nWe could use setitimer or timer_create, but we won\u0027t be able to check siginfo.timerid against anything.",
      "parentUuid": "92f10b47_8dfe5d71",
      "revId": "4ce232b7cf962a9d52cd864532ac2b6159201837",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4adf1f1d_72596ba2",
        "filename": "snapshot/linux/exception_snapshot_linux_test.cc",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 173,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-01T21:27:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e The timer_t used by (g)libc (secretly a pointer to an internal timer struct) is not the same as the __kernel_timer_t we expect to get in Codes()[0].\n\u003e \n\u003e We could use setitimer or timer_create, but we won\u0027t be able to check siginfo.timerid against anything.\n\nGot it. Better validation is a good reason to use the raw syscall in a test.",
      "parentUuid": "3ec8a9a2_07263a21",
      "revId": "4ce232b7cf962a9d52cd864532ac2b6159201837",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
